- The controller returns response()->turboStream(...). Turbo Stream responses use the media type text/vnd.turbo-stream.html and consist of HTML fragments containing one or more <turbo-stream> elements. The return type in the method signature is MultiplePendingTurboStreamResponse, confirming a Turbo Stream response is returned (with content).
- The endpoint has a path parameter {post}, which is a Post route-model-binding key (commonly an ID or slug). The path parameter is required.
- No request body is used by the controller; the method operates based on the path parameter and the authenticated user (authentication is not visible in the provided file, so security is not declared here).
- The response is a successful 200 response with Turbo Stream content (not 204), because the controller returns view and update turbo-stream elements.

